content.description: Fantastic onsite for a new 5.8 leader, very heady while being very easy and safe.  So exposed right off the deck!  Be brave, the holds are giant!
content.location: this is the arete/prow on the climber's right.  right most climb of the crag... several undocumented bolted slab climbs exist to the right here...

content.description: Ok, there is a top rope anchor installed at the top of the black, blank wall immediately left of moonah luna.  We did not install these anchors and have not had the chance to TR the climbs yet.  They look to be hard 11's or 12's

Climber's right/ downhill from "We met ouimet"  is a large area of slabs, then a vertical wall.  At the far right of the vertical wall is the first route done thus far.  It climbs the shield that terminates the cliff and it is a very good, short sport climb.  Harder than it looks!
content.location: If you walked up to the dog wall from the piles this is the first route you'd encounter.  we intend to give it "neighbors" over time

climbs.name: Ok Balto, hike!
climbs.fa: Jonathan O'Brien, Bobby Scott, Katherine Sheehan, Chilly Dog.  July 2010

content.description:
This is the dihedral on the backside of We met ouimet.  Glacier polished gray on the left-facing part of the corner.

Balto was the best lead dog we ever had and you say "hike" to get him going!
content.protection: 2 bolts, then I used a green c3/ or stopper, purple c4, red c4 and draws for the anchor.
content.location: the rightmost corner, can't miss it!

climbs.name: Moonah Luna
climbs.fa: Jonathan O'Brien, Bobby Scott, Katherine Sheehan

content.description: The pride of the crag, a beautiful crack trad climb. Strenuous to climb/protect for the grade, find those good jams! Named after our very best friends Moon and Luna.
content.protection: Gear to bolted anchor.  I used a red link cam, 2 green c4's, 3 purple c4's, and a handsize piece up top

content.description: immediately left of "ok balto, hike!"  is a top rope (unfinished sport climb)  figured i'd tell y'all that there's a TR anchor above it if anyone wants to work it out... please allow us to sink the bolts
content.protection: TR for now...  you can access it by rapping the Moonah Luna anchors skiers left

content.description: On the far left end of the crag there is a noticeable "butt crack"  route named for our most significant mother (you figure out the name, she had LOTS of puppies;)
content.protection: Gear.  lots of options.  This route is J-Tree painful down low.  bolted anchors above w/ no rap, walk off climber's left until we add the rap station.

content.description: just left of mini corner, just right of moonah luna.  again, unfinished but there's TR anchors!  its the double seam
content.protection: TR for now...  please don't add bolts, we're working on it
